text: I need some help please. Any of the exercises somehow change the breathing pattern after it starts. For example, I start anti-appetite, it automatically does three patterns: inhale, exhale, and sustain. Then, in a cycle or two, the pattern changes to: inhale and exhale only. Am I doing something wrong? Is it suppose to change patterns? Thank you for the great work you guys do.
replyText:
Daniel, thanks!
The thing you're experiencing is absolutely normal - it is called Dynamic mode of the training. It's very useful for gradual improvement in breathing gymnastics.
You can read more here: http://pranabreath.info/wiki/index.php/Dynamic_tab

text: This is the best breath app I could find after much research. It is programmable to a high degree and that is a huge plus, but also requires that one take time to do so. The only suggestion I have is to allow programming the preparation time as well so that one can have as much as a 30 minute delay before beginning the practice. replyText:
Shalom, thanks for your detailed feedback!
Preparation time is now 10 sec maximum, as I doubt if anyone looks at the screen for that long before starting the breathing session. Anyway, you can set 2 reminders: 30 min before and right before the practice.
